Let $A=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
-1 & 2 & 1 \\ 
7 & 1 & 0 \end{array}
\right)$,  $B=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-1 & 1 \\ 
7 & 1 \\ 
2 & 0 \end{array}
\right),$ and $C=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-1 & 2 \\ 
0 & 1 \end{array}
\right)$. Which of the following statements is correct?

answer1:
$\left| \begin{array}{rrr}
a & b & c \\ 
a & b & c \\ 
d & e & f \end{array}
\right|=0 $

answer2:
$\left| \begin{array}{rrr}
a & b & c \\ 
-d & -e & -f \\ 
g & h & i \end{array}
\right|=\left| \begin{array}{rrr}
a & b & c \\ 
d & e & f \\ 
g & h & i \end{array}
\right|$

answer3:
$\left| \begin{array}{rrr}
a & b & c \\ 
d & e & f \\ 
g & h & i \end{array}
\right|=-\left| \begin{array}{rrr}
a & d & g \\ 
b & e & h \\ 
c & f & i \end{array}
\right|$

answer4:
$\left| \begin{array}{rrr}
k \cdot a & k\cdot b & k\cdot c \\ 
k\cdot d & k\cdot e & k\cdot f \\ 
k\cdot g & k\cdot h & k\cdot i \end{array}
\right|=k\cdot \left| \begin{array}{rrr}
a & b & c \\ 
d & e & f \\ 
g & h & i \end{array}
\right|$

